03/03/2003
LARNACA, Cyprus -- US State Department Co-ordinator for Cyprus Thomas Weston said Sunday (2 March) he was encouraged about prospects for a resolution of the Cyprus dispute. He added that the US administration would do anything necessary to encourage acceptance of the plan proposed by UN Secretary General Kofi Annan. The deadline has been extended to 30 March. Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash remains sceptical of the plan. (CAN - 02/03/03)
